Question 7: Write an SQL query on Sales_Transactions to list all duplicate keys and 
their counts. The business key is defined as Customer_ID + Product_ID + 
Txn_Date + Txn_Amount. The query groups by these columns and filters for counts 
greater than 1. 
SQL 
SELECT  
Customer_ID,  
Product_ID,  
Txn_Date,  
Txn_Amount,  
COUNT(*) as Duplicate_Count 
FROM Sales_Transactions 
GROUP BY Customer_ID, Product_ID, Txn_Date, Txn_Amount 
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1; 
