Question 8: Enforcing Referential Integrity 
● Scenario: Identify Customer_ID values in Sales_Transactions that do not exist 
in the Customers_Master table. 
● Analysis of Data: 
○ Customers_Master contains: C101, C102, C103, C104. 
○ Sales_Transactions contains: C101, C102, C103, C104, C105, C106. 
○ Violations: C105 and C106 exist in transactions but are missing from the 
master list. 
● SQL Query to Detect Violations: 
SQL 
SELECT DISTINCT s.Customer_ID 
FROM Sales_Transactions s 
LEFT JOIN Customers_Master c ON s.Customer_ID = c.CustomerID 
WHERE c.CustomerID IS NULL; 

